{"TopicId":32120,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Please show me some instruments that can detect underground formations.","CreatedByName":"Cesrate","CreatedById":57343,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-09T08:09:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Cesrate","CreatedById":57343,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-09T08:09:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ETitle is the question.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OtherDalfite","CreatedById":8317,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-09T08:13:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWell, there is a sonar type instrument that sends down a signal through certain densities such as dirt and bounces off once it reaches something dense like stone or wood. It\u0027s used by Archeologists when scanning certain buildings with a cellar/basement that isn\u0027t directly connected to the structure. Sorry, as I can\u0027t remember it\u0027s name.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"N3X15","CreatedById":12073,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-09T08:23:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESeismometers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.lpi.usra.edu/lunar/missions/apollo/apollo_15/experiments/ps/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.lpi.usra.edu/lunar/missions/apollo/apollo_15/experiments/ps/\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlso used on Earth to \u0022see\u0022 the transitions between different types of rocks, find oil reservoirs, etc. Like OtherDalfite says, the process is much like sonar, except the pulses are from earthquakes.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cesrate","CreatedById":57343,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-09T09:00:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOh... I think what I need is OtherDalfite\u0027s archaeological instruments. But problem is we all don\u0027t remember the name.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-09T09:53:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ground-penetrating_radar\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ground-penetrating_radar\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat should do \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"softweir","CreatedById":2795,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-09T09:57:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAlso:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnetic_survey_(archaeology)\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnetic_survey_(archaeology)\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electrical_resistance_survey_(archaeology)\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electrical_resistance_survey_(archaeology)\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cesrate","CreatedById":57343,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-09T10:04:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOh thanks.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}